<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-18T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-18T09:00:00-05:00" n="527" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/4533: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-18T09:00:00-05:00">December 18, 1933—9
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>524. Dr. Grau expressed a desire to meet me yesterday and I
                                accordingly called at the Palace last night.</p>
                            <p>The press having learned of the visit I stated that I had merely told
                                Dr. Grau that Mr. Caffery would arrive this morning.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Matthews</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>